<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-04-11T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-04-11T14:00:00-05:00" n="495" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d495">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">740.00119 Control (Korea)/4–1146: Circular
                            telegram</note>
                        <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to
                                Certain <gloss type="to">Diplomatic Officers</gloss></hi><note n="79" xml:id="d495fn1">At Chungking.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#left"><hi rend="smallcaps">secret</hi></seg>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-04-11T14:00:00-05:00">April 11, 1946—2
                                p.m.</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Joint US–USSR Commission Seoul deadlocked Apr 9. US final position: It
                            will not hold dislike of Moscow communiqué (trusteeship) as criterion of
                            acceptability of parties to be consulted in formation provisional govt.
                            USSR final position: It will not speak to or consult with any party
                            which has opposed Moscow communiqué.</p>
                        <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi></signed></closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>